WEBVTT	#Elemental Media Engine(TM) 2.17.0.0

00:00:00.00 --> 00:00:03.34
We begin with the latest from the Russia-Ukraine border.

00:00:03.34 --> 00:00:05.01
Secretary of State Antony Blinken

00:00:05.01 --> 00:00:08.40
said today there has been, quote, "no meaningful pullback"

00:00:08.40 --> 00:00:11.34
of Russian troops and that Russian President Vladimir

00:00:11.34 --> 00:00:14.34
Putin could move in at any time.

00:00:14.34 --> 00:00:16.89
For more, I want to bring in Ambassador of the European

00:00:16.89 --> 00:00:19.68
Union to the United States, Stavros Lambrinidis.

00:00:19.68 --> 00:00:21.96
Mr Ambassador, it's great to see you.

00:00:21.96 --> 00:00:23.16
Help us set the stage.

00:00:23.16 --> 00:00:24.93
I think most Americans have a hard time,

00:00:24.93 --> 00:00:27.96
maybe Europeans do too, sifting through all the news

00:00:27.96 --> 00:00:30.66
about troop movements, diplomacy, rhetoric.

00:00:30.66 --> 00:00:34.72
From your vantage point, Mr Ambassador, where are we?

00:00:34.72 --> 00:00:37.72
We're in a very tense situation, and this hasn't changed.

00:00:37.72 --> 00:00:40.21
The Russian troops are still there.

00:00:40.21 --> 00:00:45.19
Even if they have removed a few, which has not been verified,

00:00:45.19 --> 00:00:48.20
we're talking about over 100,000 troops.

00:00:48.20 --> 00:00:49.66
And we're having also the situation

00:00:49.66 --> 00:00:51.88
on the ground in Ukraine that, even

00:00:51.88 --> 00:00:55.34
before any military action, is, of course, very problematic.

00:00:55.34 --> 00:00:58.27
The economy is suffering dramatically.

00:00:58.27 --> 00:01:00.52
We see cyber attacks of major scale.

00:01:00.52 --> 00:01:03.91
And we also, frankly, see people--

00:01:03.91 --> 00:01:06.86
people who are at their homes today with a bag

00:01:06.86 --> 00:01:08.32
packed in the entrance in the event

00:01:08.32 --> 00:01:10.30
they have to evacuate their own house.

00:01:10.30 --> 00:01:12.22
There's also a real human tragedy.

00:01:12.22 --> 00:01:17.65
And this is not the 1940s, this is 2022.

00:01:17.65 --> 00:01:20.11
And this is just simply unacceptable.

00:01:20.11 --> 00:01:21.73
Mr Ambassador, there were reports today

00:01:21.73 --> 00:01:23.74
of field hospitals being deployed.

00:01:23.74 --> 00:01:27.76
Does that give you any higher level of concern?

00:01:27.76 --> 00:01:30.55
Well, we've had these reports for a while.

00:01:30.55 --> 00:01:35.50
Look, I know that yesterday some signs of possible

00:01:35.50 --> 00:01:38.83
hope when Russia seemed to recognize

00:01:38.83 --> 00:01:41.86
the validity of the Minsk Agreements and the need

00:01:41.86 --> 00:01:46.72
to continue discussing the fact that they said they would be

00:01:46.72 --> 00:01:48.85
finally sending a response to the letters

00:01:48.85 --> 00:01:53.11
that NATO and the US sent to them with the proposals

00:01:53.11 --> 00:01:55.18
of the European security.

00:01:55.18 --> 00:01:57.46
At the same time, we're seeing many mixed signals.

00:01:57.46 --> 00:02:01.75
The Duma yesterday in Russia asked President Putin

00:02:01.75 --> 00:02:06.11
to recognize it as the pendant republics, Donetsk and Luhansk.

00:02:06.11 --> 00:02:11.71
So, frankly, look, this is a crisis that Russia created.

00:02:11.71 --> 00:02:14.57
We did not seek confrontation.

00:02:14.57 --> 00:02:18.19
But we are totally prepared for it if it comes to that.

00:02:18.19 --> 00:02:22.24
I think all of us here hope that Russia will not move to war,

00:02:22.24 --> 00:02:25.00
will not bring violence again to Europe.

00:02:25.00 --> 00:02:28.43
But if it does, it will face massive consequences.

00:02:28.43 --> 00:02:30.01
And it will feel them.

00:02:30.01 --> 00:02:31.87
Mr Ambassador, from an EU perspective,

00:02:31.87 --> 00:02:32.89
what are the dangers--

00:02:32.89 --> 00:02:35.41
economic, humanitarian, and otherwise--

00:02:35.41 --> 00:02:38.75
of a full-blown Russian invasion?

00:02:38.75 --> 00:02:41.62
The immediate dangers are very clear,

00:02:41.62 --> 00:02:43.30
and we are preparing for them, including

00:02:43.30 --> 00:02:45.94
for a humanitarian crisis in Ukraine,

00:02:45.94 --> 00:02:49.61
for ensuring that we deal with any flows of people coming out.

00:02:49.61 --> 00:02:51.52
But we have not given up on diplomacy,

00:02:51.52 --> 00:02:54.70
as you can tell also from visits by the German

00:02:54.70 --> 00:02:59.38
Chancellor, the French President, and others.

00:02:59.38 --> 00:03:01.95
We do not think diplomacy is over.

00:03:01.95 --> 00:03:03.37
But in order for it to work, we're

00:03:03.37 --> 00:03:05.53
also signaling to Russia very clearly

00:03:05.53 --> 00:03:09.07
that the consequences, if it chooses the path of war,

00:03:09.07 --> 00:03:10.24
will be massive.

00:03:10.24 --> 00:03:14.26
And Europeans, the 27 member states of the European Union

00:03:14.26 --> 00:03:17.14
are, perhaps in an unprecedented way,

00:03:17.14 --> 00:03:20.14
united behind the European Commission

00:03:20.14 --> 00:03:23.35
in having put in place and discussing

00:03:23.35 --> 00:03:28.03
the extent of robust, coordinated, massive sanctions

00:03:28.03 --> 00:03:29.12
against Russia.

00:03:29.12 --> 00:03:32.71
So for us, this is existential.

00:03:32.71 --> 00:03:35.68
It must be understood, this is Europe.

00:03:35.68 --> 00:03:38.41
And Ukraine is in Europe.

00:03:38.41 --> 00:03:42.10
And Russia is not just simply threatening Ukraine.

00:03:42.10 --> 00:03:44.44
But through Ukraine, it is, in effect,

00:03:44.44 --> 00:03:48.13
threatening the right of countries in the 21st century

00:03:48.13 --> 00:03:51.86
to be free, and independent, and to make their own decisions.

00:03:51.86 --> 00:03:55.25
If that kind of blood affair succeeds,

00:03:55.25 --> 00:03:58.66
then instability, and insecurity, and the potential

00:03:58.66 --> 00:04:02.20
for war, not just in Europe, in the rest of the world,

00:04:02.20 --> 00:04:03.94
is going to be much higher.

00:04:03.94 --> 00:04:08.14
Might is not right, and we will make sure

00:04:08.14 --> 00:04:11.53
that Russia, one way or the other, understands this.

00:04:11.53 --> 00:04:14.65
Mr Ambassador, as a side issue, I

00:04:14.65 --> 00:04:17.17
want to talk about energy and leverage.

00:04:17.17 --> 00:04:21.10
There has been some commentary that Europe's move

00:04:21.10 --> 00:04:24.91
toward renewable energy, for all sorts of understandable climate

00:04:24.91 --> 00:04:27.94
change reasons, has left it without a reliable bridge

00:04:27.94 --> 00:04:30.07
supply of fossil fuels.

00:04:30.07 --> 00:04:32.62
And that has increased Russian leverage.

00:04:32.62 --> 00:04:38.32
Agree, disagree that that is part of this larger equation?

00:04:38.32 --> 00:04:39.37
Absolutely disagree.

00:04:39.37 --> 00:04:40.93
But let me tell you something.

00:04:40.93 --> 00:04:45.22
Russia has shown, even before this war crisis,

00:04:45.22 --> 00:04:48.85
to be an unreliable supplier of gas to Europe.

00:04:48.85 --> 00:04:54.85
And Europe, in fact, is ensuring its independence from Russia

00:04:54.85 --> 00:04:58.81
by focusing on the energy resources that it can home

00:04:58.81 --> 00:05:01.96
produce, which are, in fact, clean energy.

00:05:01.96 --> 00:05:05.41
And what we have done in the past few months

00:05:05.41 --> 00:05:09.01
has actually also very effective in ensuring

00:05:09.01 --> 00:05:11.47
that if Russia decides to weaponize energy

00:05:11.47 --> 00:05:14.59
in this particular crisis, we will be ready.

00:05:14.59 --> 00:05:19.96
The imports of liquefied natural gas from many different sources

00:05:19.96 --> 00:05:23.08
around the world in the past month

00:05:23.08 --> 00:05:25.31
have increased at record levels.

00:05:25.31 --> 00:05:31.27
We have built LNG terminals all over Europe since the 2014

00:05:31.27 --> 00:05:33.16
invasion in Crimea.

00:05:33.16 --> 00:05:37.57
And we are also massively expanding our electricity

00:05:37.57 --> 00:05:39.16
interconnectors in Europe.

00:05:39.16 --> 00:05:41.47
And that is going to allow us to take

00:05:41.47 --> 00:05:43.48
all of that source of energy from LNG

00:05:43.48 --> 00:05:46.12
and from the green sources and to transfer it

00:05:46.12 --> 00:05:47.35
in every corner of Europe.

00:05:47.35 --> 00:05:49.75
We are entirely sure that this winter,

00:05:49.75 --> 00:05:52.31
no matter what Russia does, we are OK.

00:05:52.31 --> 00:05:53.92
But we are building for the future.

00:05:53.92 --> 00:05:57.46
If anything, this crisis shows that when we have committed

00:05:57.46 --> 00:06:00.61
to move to green energy in the European Union,

00:06:00.61 --> 00:06:04.12
this is not just a supremely important decision

00:06:04.12 --> 00:06:07.43
for the future growth of the EU and for the world,

00:06:07.43 --> 00:06:10.03
not just a supremely important decision for the planet

00:06:10.03 --> 00:06:13.15
itself and for humans living on it, frankly,

00:06:13.15 --> 00:06:17.11
but also a strategically important decision, which

00:06:17.11 --> 00:06:20.08
is why when President Biden and the European Commission

00:06:20.08 --> 00:06:22.51
president Von der Leyen issued a joint statement

00:06:22.51 --> 00:06:24.94
a couple of weeks ago on this exact topic,

00:06:24.94 --> 00:06:27.10
they focused both on energy security

00:06:27.10 --> 00:06:30.34
and on the importance of the US and the EU moving

00:06:30.34 --> 00:06:33.23
to a clean energy transition.

00:06:33.23 --> 00:06:35.89
So picking up on that point, Mr Ambassador,

00:06:35.89 --> 00:06:38.05
I wonder if it, from your perspective,

00:06:38.05 --> 00:06:41.92
appears that NATO has been re-energized,

00:06:41.92 --> 00:06:46.27
Europe had already focused, as you mentioned, since 2014,

00:06:46.27 --> 00:06:48.55
on more energy independence from Russia.

00:06:48.55 --> 00:06:51.19
But it's certainly accelerated that process, and maybe

00:06:51.19 --> 00:06:54.28
the political will to do so has intensified.

00:06:54.28 --> 00:06:57.44
Taking those two things just by themselves,

00:06:57.44 --> 00:07:00.74
is Russia making a huge miscalculation here?

00:07:00.74 --> 00:07:01.97
I think so.

00:07:01.97 --> 00:07:02.79
I really think so.

00:07:02.79 --> 00:07:05.72
I think Russia thought it could divide and conquer us.

00:07:05.72 --> 00:07:08.81
And it has actually united the European Union and NATO

00:07:08.81 --> 00:07:14.01
more than we have arguably been ever before.

00:07:14.01 --> 00:07:18.12
And just to give you just one example of that unity.

00:07:18.12 --> 00:07:19.58
Foreign minister of Russia, Lavrov,

00:07:19.58 --> 00:07:23.84
sent 36 letters to the 36 countries of the European Union

00:07:23.84 --> 00:07:27.74
and of NATO, asking them to answer separately

00:07:27.74 --> 00:07:30.32
to his analysis about what the indivisibility

00:07:30.32 --> 00:07:33.77
of European security is, clearly hoping to divide and conquer.

00:07:33.77 --> 00:07:37.04
He sent 36 letters, he received two replies.

00:07:37.04 --> 00:07:40.67
One from Josep Borrell, the European Union's Foreign Policy

00:07:40.67 --> 00:07:44.93
Chief on behalf of every single one of the 27 EU member states,

00:07:44.93 --> 00:07:46.88
and one from the Secretary General

00:07:46.88 --> 00:07:49.04
of NATO, Mr. Stoltenberg.

00:07:49.04 --> 00:07:54.77
Now, if Russia needed more proof that its attempts to divide

00:07:54.77 --> 00:07:59.03
are failing, it couldn't have gotten a clearer signal.

00:07:59.03 --> 00:08:00.40
You have implied this, but I just

00:08:00.40 --> 00:08:02.32
want to nail you down on this, Mr Ambassador--

00:08:02.32 --> 00:08:05.53
that the European Union and Europe broadly will

00:08:05.53 --> 00:08:08.47
unhesitatingly join the United States

00:08:08.47 --> 00:08:10.63
in the unprecedented economic sanctions

00:08:10.63 --> 00:08:14.92
President Biden has promised if, in fact, Russia invades.

00:08:14.92 --> 00:08:16.06
The answer is, yes.

00:08:16.06 --> 00:08:18.58
And if you like, one more thing that maybe President Putin

00:08:18.58 --> 00:08:22.01
was not counting on is how remarkable the coordination

00:08:22.01 --> 00:08:24.01
between the European Union and the United States

00:08:24.01 --> 00:08:26.99
has been during this crisis.

00:08:26.99 --> 00:08:31.06
We are speaking almost every day at the highest levels

00:08:31.06 --> 00:08:35.68
and technical levels to nail down all the consequences

00:08:35.68 --> 00:08:37.42
that Russia will face.

00:08:37.42 --> 00:08:41.21
We have committed to massive and coordinated sanctions.

00:08:41.21 --> 00:08:43.63
They will not just simply touch individuals, although they

00:08:43.63 --> 00:08:45.20
will touch those as well.

00:08:45.20 --> 00:08:48.37
But they will touch also major areas

00:08:48.37 --> 00:08:52.01
of the Russian economy, whether it is energy,

00:08:52.01 --> 00:08:55.45
or whether it is the financial sector.

00:08:55.45 --> 00:09:00.01
And most importantly, they will also deal a major blow

00:09:00.01 --> 00:09:05.29
to Russia's hope to wean its economy away from the gas

00:09:05.29 --> 00:09:07.78
that it has now, and the oil, and do something else,

00:09:07.78 --> 00:09:10.09
because they will need the technology

00:09:10.09 --> 00:09:14.41
that the US and the EU have, almost exclusively to do so,

00:09:14.41 --> 00:09:16.82
and they will not be getting it.

00:09:16.82 --> 00:09:19.90
So this, we tell Russia all the time and the Russian people,

00:09:19.90 --> 00:09:21.91
is not the only path.

00:09:21.91 --> 00:09:25.51
If Russia does not choose war, and it's in its hands

00:09:25.51 --> 00:09:26.83
entirely to do so--

00:09:26.83 --> 00:09:29.11
if it chooses the negotiation path,

00:09:29.11 --> 00:09:31.33
there is a bright potential future

00:09:31.33 --> 00:09:33.67
in this relationship that will bring prosperity

00:09:33.67 --> 00:09:35.14
to the Russian people.

00:09:35.14 --> 00:09:37.69
And this is precisely what we are committed to.

00:09:37.69 --> 00:09:42.02
But if it chooses war, as I said before, we are prepared.

00:09:42.02 --> 00:09:44.56
I must tell you, Mr Ambassador, in my conversations this week

00:09:44.56 --> 00:09:46.60
here in Washington with lawmakers,

00:09:46.60 --> 00:09:50.26
briefed by the White House, they would, I would say,

00:09:50.26 --> 00:09:54.91
describe themselves as gloomy, expecting an invasion maybe

00:09:54.91 --> 00:09:56.56
this week, maybe this weekend.

00:09:56.56 --> 00:10:00.67
And they fear Russia won't stop after Ukraine.

00:10:00.67 --> 00:10:02.85
What is your assessment?

00:10:02.85 --> 00:10:05.37
Well, precisely because we share the same fear.

00:10:05.37 --> 00:10:08.85
I said before that this is an existential crisis for us.

00:10:08.85 --> 00:10:12.60
And it is exactly the reason that you see the European

00:10:12.60 --> 00:10:15.63
Union so remarkably strong and united

00:10:15.63 --> 00:10:18.69
behind averting this crisis.

00:10:18.69 --> 00:10:21.78
I am not, and Mr. Putin said no one is--

00:10:21.78 --> 00:10:24.15
I do not know what he's thinking about.

00:10:24.15 --> 00:10:25.92
But the fact of the matter is that he does

00:10:25.92 --> 00:10:29.31
have two paths to choose from.

00:10:29.31 --> 00:10:32.07
And the fact of the matter is that if he thought

00:10:32.07 --> 00:10:34.23
that what he is doing now is going

00:10:34.23 --> 00:10:36.60
to do anything other than strengthen NATO

00:10:36.60 --> 00:10:38.73
and strengthen the European Union,

00:10:38.73 --> 00:10:40.72
he has failed in that calculation.

00:10:40.72 --> 00:10:44.46
So I do believe, as I said at the beginning,

00:10:44.46 --> 00:10:46.90
that we are still in a major crisis.

00:10:46.90 --> 00:10:49.68
And I do believe that it's entirely possible that Russia

00:10:49.68 --> 00:10:52.68
will choose the path to war.

00:10:52.68 --> 00:10:55.68
And this is why the signal we're sending to them

00:10:55.68 --> 00:11:01.93
is if you do so, it's going to be a remarkable violent period

00:11:01.93 --> 00:11:04.57
for Europe that is going to cost you,

00:11:04.57 --> 00:11:09.25
both in real economic terms and historically,

00:11:09.25 --> 00:11:11.92
a price that you've never paid in the recent history

00:11:11.92 --> 00:11:12.82
of Russia.

00:11:12.82 --> 00:11:15.28
It's going to ensure that Europe, which

00:11:15.28 --> 00:11:20.11
is Russia's neighbor, is going to move away from Russia

00:11:20.11 --> 00:11:22.19
for a very long time.

00:11:22.19 --> 00:11:23.65
It's going to assure that Russia is

00:11:23.65 --> 00:11:25.82
going to suffer economic consequences they will have

00:11:25.82 --> 00:11:29.44
to claw out of, perhaps by seeking alliances

00:11:29.44 --> 00:11:31.49
around the world that in normal circumstances,

00:11:31.49 --> 00:11:34.06
it would feel quite uncomfortable in.

00:11:34.06 --> 00:11:38.35
And it will mean that the Russian people, who absolutely

00:11:38.35 --> 00:11:45.73
have nothing to be blamed for for the Kremlin's adventurism

00:11:45.73 --> 00:11:47.32
may also suffer in return.

00:11:47.32 --> 00:11:50.02
And that is just simply something we do not want.

00:11:50.02 --> 00:11:53.59
It's entirely Mr. Putin's decision.

00:11:53.59 --> 00:11:55.82
Stavros Lambrinidis, the European Union Ambassador

00:11:55.82 --> 00:11:56.74
to the United States--

00:11:56.74 --> 00:11:58.84
Mr Ambassador, thank you so much for your time

00:11:58.84 --> 00:12:00.05
and your perspective.

00:12:00.05 --> 00:12:01.98
Thank you very much.